00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:03,139
And our last phrase, and this is kind of an expression, right?

240
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:04,700
Goodness sake.

241
00:13:04,820 --> 00:13:05,799
For goodness sake.

242
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:08,220
Okay, so let's look at the context.

243
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,600
The kids say, we're in grade seven.

244
00:13:10,799 --> 00:13:15,600
And the person at the door says, then for goodness sake, don't you see this sign?

245
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:17,620
Right, for goodness sake.

246
00:13:17,799 --> 00:13:23,539
So this is an expression that's used to indicate maybe you're a little bit frustrated.

247
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:23,919
Yes.

248
00:13:24,259 --> 00:13:24,419
Right?

249
00:13:24,779 --> 00:13:28,639
So it's like, come on, or my goodness, or for Pete's sake.

250
00:13:28,980 --> 00:13:33,679
So we have many ways of saying, all right, come on, I'm a little tired of this.

251
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:35,220
You're irritating me.

252
00:13:35,659 --> 00:13:35,720
Right.

253
00:13:35,799 --> 00:13:39,120
So basically the person's saying, you are too old for this.

254
00:13:40,019 --> 00:13:40,919
You're too old for this.

255
00:13:40,980 --> 00:13:42,580
You should read what it says on my door.

256
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:43,519
No soliciting.

257
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:43,840
Right.

258
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:44,940
And so the person's angry.

259
00:13:45,340 --> 00:13:45,440
Right.

260
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:52,580
The person's angry because these kids are trying to sell her something, when clearly she has a sign that says, no soliciting.

261
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:53,080
That's right.

262
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:53,860
Okay.

